===Other Names===
Route 37 is also known as:<ref>{{cite book | url=http://www.dot.ca.gov/hq/tsip/hseb/products/2006_Named_Freeways.pdf | title=2006 Named Freeways, Highways, Structures and Other Appurtenances in California | publisher=[[California Department of Transportation|Caltrans]] | pages=127 | accessdate=2007-03-28}}</ref>
*'''Randy Bolt Memorial Highway''': From Route 29 to Skaggs Road. ([http://www.camemorial.org/htm/bolt.htm Bolt memorial])
*'''Sears Point Toll Road''': Originally a [[toll road]], runs from Route 121 to Vallejo.

